00036             static std::string to_string(uint64_t n) {
00037                 const char *fmt = NULL;
00038                 if (n<=9) {
00039                     fmt = "%"PRIu64;
00040                 } else if (n<=0xff) {
00041                     fmt = "0x%02"PRIx64;
00042                 } else if (n<=0xffff) {
00043                     fmt = "0x%04"PRIx64;
00044                 } else {
00045                     fmt = "0x%08"PRIx64;

00052             void print(std::ostream &o) const {
00053                 if (empty()) {

00056                     o <<to_string(first());

00167                 uint64_t possible_bits() const {
00168                     uint64_t bits=0;
00169                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ii=p_intervals.begin(); ii!=p_intervals.end(); ++ii) {
00170                         uint64_t lo=ii->first.first(), hi=ii->first.last();
00171                         bits |= lo | hi;
00172                         for (uint64_t bitno=0; bitno<32; ++bitno) {
00173                             uint64_t bit = IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(bitno);
00174                             if (0 == (bits & bit)) {
00175                                 uint64_t base = lo & ~IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(bitno);
00176                                 if (ii->first.contains(Interval(base+bit)))

00178                             }
00179                         }
00180                     }

00187                 static ValueType from_bits(uint64_t possible_bits) {
00188                     static const uint64_t max_complexity = 50; // arbitrary
00189                     Intervals retval;
00190                     possible_bits &= IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBits);
00191 
00192                     size_t nset = 0, lobit=nBits, hibit=0;
00193                     for (size_t i=0; i<nBits; ++i) {
00194                         if (0 != (possible_bits & IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(i))) {
00195                             ++nset;
00196                             lobit = std::min(lobit, i);
00197                             hibit = std::max(hibit, i);
00198                         }
00199                     }
00200                     
00201                     if (possible_bits == IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nset)) {
00202                         // The easy case: all possible bits are grouped together at the low end.
00203                         retval.insert(Interval::inin(0, possible_bits));
00204                     } else {
00205                         // Low-order bit of result must be clear, so the rangemap will have 2^nset ranges
00206                         uint64_t nranges = IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(nset); // 2^nset
00207                         if (nranges>max_complexity) {
00208                             uint64_t hi = IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(hibit+1) ^ IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(lobit);
00209                             retval.insert(Interval::inin(0, hi));
00210                         } else {
00211                             for (uint64_t i=0; i<nranges; ++i) {
00212                                 uint64_t lo=0, tmp=i;
00213                                 for (uint64_t j=0; j<nBits; ++j) {
00214                                     uint64_t bit = IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(j);
00215                                     if (0 != (possible_bits & bit)) {
00216                                         lo |= (tmp & 1) << j;
00217                                         tmp = tmp >> 1;
00218                                     }
00219                                 }
00220                                 retval.insert(Interval(lo));
00221                             }
00222                         }
00223                     }
00224                     return ValueType<nBits>(retval);
00225                 }
00226             };

00420                 template<size_t nBits>
00421                 ValueType<nBits> add(const ValueType<nBits> &a, const ValueType<nBits> &b) const {
00422                     const Intervals &aints=a.get_intervals(), &bints=b.get_intervals();
00423                     Intervals result;
00424                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=aints.begin(); ai!=aints.end(); ++ai) {
00425                         for (Intervals::const_iterator bi=bints.begin(); bi!=bints.end(); ++bi) {
00426                             uint64_t lo = (ai->first.first() + bi->first.first()) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBits>::value;
00427                             uint64_t hi = (ai->first.last()  + bi->first.last())  & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBits>::value;
00428                             if (lo < ai->first.first() || lo < bi->first.first()) {
00429                                 // lo and hi both overflow
00430                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00431                             } else if (hi < ai->first.last() || hi < bi->first.last()) {
00432                                 // hi overflows, but not lo
00433                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBits)));
00434                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(0, hi));
00435                             } else {
00436                                 // no overflow
00437                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00438                             }
00439                         }
00440                     }
00441                     return ValueType<nBits>(result);
00442                 }

00445                 template<size_t nBits>
00446                 ValueType<nBits> addWithCarries(const ValueType<nBits> &a, const ValueType<nBits> &b, const ValueType<1> &c,
00447                                                 ValueType<nBits> &carry_out) const {
00448                     ValueType<nBits> wide_carry = unsignedExtend<1, nBits>(c);
00449                     ValueType<nBits> retval = add(add(a, b), wide_carry);
00450 
00451                     uint64_t known1 = a.is_known() ? a.known_value() : 0;
00452                     uint64_t known2 = b.is_known() ? b.known_value() : 0;
00453                     uint64_t known3 = c.is_known() ? c.known_value() : 0;
00454                     uint64_t unkwn1 = a.is_known() ? 0 : a.possible_bits();
00455                     uint64_t unkwn2 = b.is_known() ? 0 : b.possible_bits();
00456                     uint64_t unkwn3 = c.is_known() ? 0 : c.possible_bits();
00457                     enum Carry { C_FALSE, C_TRUE, C_UNKNOWN };
00458                     Carry cin = C_FALSE; // carry propagated across loop iterations
00459                     uint64_t known_co=0, unkwn_co=0; // known or possible carry-out bits
00460                     for (size_t i=0; i<nBits; ++i, known1>>=1, known2>>=1, known3>>=1, unkwn1>>=1, unkwn2>>=1, unkwn3>>=1) {
00461                         int known_sum = (known1 & 1) + (known2 & 1) + (known3 & 1) + (C_TRUE==cin ? 1 : 0);
00462                         int unkwn_sum = (unkwn1 & 1) + (unkwn2 & 1) + (unkwn3 & 1) + (C_UNKNOWN==cin ? 1 : 0);
00463                         if (known_sum>1) {
00464                             known_co |= IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(i);
00465                             cin = C_TRUE;
00466                         } else if (known_sum + unkwn_sum > 1) {
00467                             unkwn_co |= IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(i);
00468                             cin = C_UNKNOWN;
00469                         }
00470                     }
00471                     if (unkwn_co) {
00472                         carry_out = ValueType<nBits>::from_bits(known_co | unkwn_co);
00473                     } else {
00474                         carry_out = ValueType<nBits>(known_co);
00475                     }
00476                     return retval;
00477                 }

00480                 template<size_t nBits>
00481                 ValueType<nBits> and_(const ValueType<nBits> &a, const ValueType<nBits> &b) const {
00482                     uint64_t ak = a.is_known() ? a.known_value() : 0;
00483                     uint64_t bk = b.is_known() ? b.known_value() : 0;
00484                     uint64_t au = a.is_known() ? 0 : a.possible_bits();
00485                     uint64_t bu = b.is_known() ? 0 : b.possible_bits();

00487                     if (au || bu)
00488                         return ValueType<nBits>::from_bits(r);

00517                 template<size_t BeginBit, size_t EndBit, size_t nBitsA>
00518                 ValueType<EndBit-BeginBit> extract(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a) const {
00519                     using namespace IntegerOps;
00520                     Intervals result;
00521                     uint64_t discard_mask = ~GenMask<uint64_t, EndBit>::value; // hi-order bits being discarded
00522                     uint64_t src_mask = GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value; // significant bits in the source operand
00523                     uint64_t dst_mask = GenMask<uint64_t, EndBit-BeginBit>::value; // sig. bits in the result
00524                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00525                         const Interval &iv = ai->first;
00526                         uint64_t d1 = shiftRightLogical<nBitsA>(iv.first() & discard_mask, EndBit); // discarded part, lo
00527                         uint64_t d2 = shiftRightLogical<nBitsA>(iv.last()  & discard_mask, EndBit); // discarded part, hi
00528                         uint64_t k1 = shiftRightLogical<nBitsA>(iv.first() & src_mask, BeginBit) & dst_mask; // keep part, lo
00529                         uint64_t k2 = shiftRightLogical<nBitsA>(iv.last()  & src_mask, BeginBit) & dst_mask; // keep part, hi
00530                         if (d1==d2) {                   // no overflow in the kept bits
00531                             assert(k1<=k2);
00532                             result.insert(Interval::inin(k1, k2));
00533                         } else if (d1+1<d2 || k1<k2) {  // complete overflow
00534                             result.insert(Interval::inin(0, dst_mask));
00535                             break;
00536                         } else {                        // partial overflow
00537                             result.insert(Interval::inin(0, k2));
00538                             result.insert(Interval::inin(k1, dst_mask));
00539                         }
00540                     }
00541                     return ValueType<EndBit-BeginBit>(result);
00542                 }

00545                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00546                 ValueType<nBitsA+nBitsB> concat(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00547                     Intervals result;
00548                     uint64_t mask_a = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00549                     uint64_t mask_b = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsB>::value;
00550                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00551                         for (Intervals::const_iterator bi=b.get_intervals().begin(); bi!=b.get_intervals().end(); ++bi) {
00552                             uint64_t lo = (IntegerOps::shiftLeft<nBitsA+nBitsB>(bi->first.first() & mask_b, nBitsA) |
00553                                            (ai->first.first() & mask_a));
00554                             uint64_t hi = (IntegerOps::shiftLeft<nBitsA+nBitsB>(bi->first.last() & mask_b, nBitsA) |
00555                                            (ai->first.last() & mask_a));
00556                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00557                         }
00558                     }
00559                     return ValueType<nBitsA+nBitsB>(result);
00560                 }

00573                 template<size_t nBits>
00574                 ValueType<nBits> leastSignificantSetBit(const ValueType<nBits> &a) const {
00575                     if (a.is_known()) {

00577                         if (av) {

00588                     uint64_t lo=nBits, hi=0;

00590                         if (abits & IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(i)) {
00591                             lo = std::min(lo, (uint64_t)i);
00592                             hi = std::max(hi, (uint64_t)i);

00594                     }

00634                     uint64_t mask = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBits>::value;
00635                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00636                         const Interval &iv = ai->first;
00637                         uint64_t lo = -iv.last() & mask;
00638                         uint64_t hi = -iv.first() & mask;
00639                         if (0==hi) {
00640                             assert(0==iv.first());
00641                             result.insert(Interval(0));
00642                             if (0!=lo) {
00643                                 assert(0!=iv.last());
00644                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBits>::value));
00645                             }
00646                         } else {
00647                             assert(lo<=hi);
00648                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00649                         }
00650                     }
00651                     return ValueType<nBits>(result);
00652                 }

00655                 template<size_t nBits>
00656                 ValueType<nBits> or_(const ValueType<nBits> &a, const ValueType<nBits> &b) const {
00657                     if (a.is_known() && b.is_known()) {
00658                         uint64_t result = a.known_value() | b.known_value();
00659                         return ValueType<nBits>(result);
00660                     }
00661                     uint64_t abits = a.possible_bits(), bbits = b.possible_bits();
00662                     uint64_t rbits = abits | bbits; // bits that could be set in the result
00663                     return ValueType<nBits>::from_bits(rbits);
00664                 }

00667                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00668                 ValueType<nBitsA> rotateLeft(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00669                     if (a.is_known() && b.is_known()) {
00670                         uint64_t bn = b.known_value();
00671                         uint64_t result = ((a.known_value() << bn) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value) |
00672                                           ((a.known_value() >> (nBitsA-bn)) & IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(bn));
00673                         return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00674                     }
00675                     uint64_t abits = a.possible_bits();
00676                     uint64_t rbits = 0, done = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00677                     for (uint64_t i=0; i<(uint64_t)nBitsA && rbits!=done; ++i) {
00678                         if (b.get_intervals().contains(Interval(i))) {
00679                             rbits |= ((abits << i) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value) |
00680                                      ((abits >> (nBitsA-i)) & IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(i));
00681                         }
00682                     }
00683                     return ValueType<nBitsA>::from_bits(rbits);
00684                 }

00690                         uint64_t bn = b.known_value();
00691                         uint64_t result = ((a.known_value() >> bn) & IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBitsA-bn)) |
00692                                           ((a.known_value() << (nBitsA-bn)) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value);

00695                     uint64_t abits = a.possible_bits();

00698                         if (b.get_intervals().contains(Interval(i))) {
00699                             rbits |= ((abits >> i) & IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBitsA-i)) |
00700                                      ((abits << (nBitsA-i)) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value);

00708                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00709                 ValueType<nBitsA> shiftLeft(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00710                     if (a.is_known() && b.is_known()) {
00711                         uint64_t result = b.known_value()<nBitsA ? a.known_value() << b.known_value() : (uint64_t)0;
00712                         return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00713                     }
00714                     uint64_t abits = a.possible_bits();
00715                     uint64_t rbits = 0, done = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00716                     for (uint64_t i=0; i<(uint64_t)nBitsA && rbits!=done; ++i) {
00717                         if (b.get_intervals().contains(Interval(i)))
00718                             rbits |= (abits << i) & IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00719                     }
00720                     return ValueType<nBitsA>::from_bits(rbits);
00721                 }

00724                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00725                 ValueType<nBitsA> shiftRight(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00726                     if (b.is_known()) {
00727                         uint64_t bn = b.known_value();
00728                         if (bn >= nBitsA)
00729                             return ValueType<nBitsA>(0);
00730                         if (a.is_known())
00731                             return ValueType<nBitsA>(a.known_value() >> bn);
00732                         Intervals result;
00733                         for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00734                             uint64_t lo = ai->first.first() >> bn;
00735                             uint64_t hi = ai->first.last() >> bn;
00736                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00737                         }
00738                         return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00739                     }
00740                     Intervals result;
00741                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00742                         for (uint64_t i=0; i<(uint64_t)nBitsA; ++i) {
00743                             if (b.get_intervals().contains(Interval(i))) {
00744                                 uint64_t lo = ai->first.first() >> i;
00745                                 uint64_t hi = ai->first.first() >> i;
00746                                 result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00747                             }
00748                         }
00749                     }
00750                     return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00751                 }

00754                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00755                 ValueType<nBitsA> shiftRightArithmetic(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00756                     if (a.is_known() && b.is_known()) {
00757                         uint64_t bn = b.known_value();
00758                         uint64_t result = a.known_value() >> bn;
00759                         if (IntegerOps::signBit<nBitsA>(a.is_known()))
00760                             result |= IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value ^ IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBitsA-bn);
00761                         return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00762                     }
00763                     uint64_t abits = a.possible_bits();
00764                     uint64_t rbits = 0, done = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00765                     for (uint64_t i=0; i<(uint64_t)nBitsA && rbits!=done; ++i) {
00766                         if (b.get_intervals().contains(Interval(i))) {
00767                             rbits |= ((abits >> i) & IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBitsA-i)) |
00768                                      (IntegerOps::signBit<nBitsA>(abits) ?
00769                                       done ^ IntegerOps::genMask<uint64_t>(nBitsA-i) : (uint64_t)0);
00770                         }
00771                     }
00772                     return ValueType<nBitsA>::from_bits(rbits);
00773                 }

00776                 template<size_t From, size_t To>
00777                 ValueType<To> signExtend(const ValueType<From> &a) {
00778                     uint64_t old_signbit = IntegerOps::SHL1<uint64_t, From-1>::value;
00779                     uint64_t new_signbit = IntegerOps::SHL1<uint64_t, To-1>::value;
00780                     Intervals result;
00781                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00782                         uint64_t lo = IntegerOps::signExtend<From, To>(ai->first.first());
00783                         uint64_t hi = IntegerOps::signExtend<From, To>(ai->first.last());
00784                         if (0==(lo & new_signbit) && 0!=(hi & new_signbit)) {
00785                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, From-1>::value));
00786                             result.insert(Interval::inin(old_signbit, hi));
00787                         } else {
00788                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00789                         }
00790                     }
00791                     return ValueType<To>(result);
00792                 }

00819                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00820                 ValueType<nBitsA> unsignedDivide(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00821                     Intervals result;
00822                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00823                         for (Intervals::const_iterator bi=b.get_intervals().begin(); bi!=b.get_intervals().end(); ++bi) {
00824                             uint64_t lo = ai->first.first() / std::max(bi->first.last(),  (uint64_t)1);
00825                             uint64_t hi = ai->first.last()  / std::max(bi->first.first(), (uint64_t)1);
00826                             assert((lo<=IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value));
00827                             assert((hi<=IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value));
00828                             assert(lo<=hi);
00829                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00830                         }
00831                     }
00832                     return ValueType<nBitsA>(result);
00833                 }

00836                 template<size_t nBitsA, size_t nBitsB>
00837                 ValueType<nBitsB> unsignedModulo(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00838                     if (b.is_known()) {
00839                         // If B is a power of two then mask away the high bits of A
00840                         uint64_t bn = b.known_value();
00841                         for (size_t i=0; i<nBitsB; ++i) {
00842                             uint64_t twopow = IntegerOps::shl1<uint64_t>(i);
00843                             if (bn==twopow) {
00844                                 uint64_t limit = IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, nBitsA>::value;
00845                                 Intervals result = a.get_intervals();
00846                                 result.erase(Interval::inin(twopow, limit));
00847                                 return ValueType<nBitsB>(result);
00848                             }
00849                         }
00850                     }
00851                     return ValueType<nBitsB>(); // FIXME: can we do better?
00852                 }

00856                 ValueType<nBitsA+nBitsB> unsignedMultiply(const ValueType<nBitsA> &a, const ValueType<nBitsB> &b) const {
00857                     Intervals result;
00858                     for (Intervals::const_iterator ai=a.get_intervals().begin(); ai!=a.get_intervals().end(); ++ai) {
00859                         for (Intervals::const_iterator bi=b.get_intervals().begin(); bi!=b.get_intervals().end(); ++bi) {
00860                             uint64_t lo = ai->first.first() * bi->first.first();
00861                             uint64_t hi = ai->first.last()  * bi->first.last();
00862                             assert(lo<=hi);
00863                             result.insert(Interval::inin(lo, hi));
00864                         }
00865                     }
00866                     return ValueType<nBitsA+nBitsB>(result);
